In[19]:
def grayscale(img):
    b,g,r = cv2.split(img)
    return 0.299*r + 0.587*g + 0.114*b

img_gray = grayscale(img)
plt.imshow(img_gray, cmap='gray')
plt.title("Grayscale")
plt.axis('off')
plt.show()
In[20]:
def add_padding(img):
    return np.pad(img,1,mode='constant', constant_values=0)

def remove_padding(img):
    return img[1:-1,1:-1]

def conv(img,kernel):
    rows,cols = img.shape
    krows,kcols = kernel.shape
    out = np.zeros_like(img).astype(int)

    img = add_padding(img)

    for i in range(rows):
        for j in range(cols):
            img_part = img[i:i+krows,j:j+kcols]
            out[i,j] = np.sum(img_part * kernel).astype(int)

    return out
In[21]:
sobel_x = np.array([[-1,0,1],[-2,0,2],[-1,0,1]])
sobel_y = np.array([[-1,-2,-1],[0,0,0],[1,2,1]])

grad_x = conv(img_gray,sobel_x)
grad_y = conv(img_gray,sobel_y)

mag = np.sqrt(grad_x**2 + grad_y**2).astype(int)
threshold = 150
edges = np.where(mag > threshold, 255, 0).astype(int)

plt.imshow(edges, cmap='grey')
plt.title("Sobel")
plt.axis('off')
plt.show()

Inference

Canny edge detection performs better than sobel, prewitt and robert for complex images but similar for simple images
